name: 16S rRNA (guanine527-N7)-methyltransferase
names: ribosomal RNA small subunit methyltransferase G
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + guanine527 in 16S rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N7-methylguanine527 in 16S rRNA
comment: The enzyme specifically methylates guanine527 at N7 in 16S rRNA.

references.title: Loss of a conserved 7-methylguanosine modification in 16S rRNA confers low-level streptomycin resistance in bacteria.
Crystal structure of the Escherichia coli glucose-inhibited division protein B (GidB) reveals a methyltransferase fold.
